Sentencas: Anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) have been extensively investigated due to their ease of fabrication, robustness, and high electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, anode supported SOFCs are fabricated and characterized as a function of the components in the anode supports.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The addition of Fe2O3 to NiO-yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) anode support tape changes the morphology of the support.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Nickel ferrite spinel from the reaction of Fe2O3 and NiO during co-firing produces spherical shaped macropores without a change in porosity.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SOFCs fabricated by the addition of 0 wt%, 5 wt%, 10 wt%, and 20 wt% Fe2O3, exhibit maximum power densities of 2.24 W cm(-2), 2.45 W cm-2, 2.38 W cm(-2), and 2.09 W cm(-2), respectively, at 800 degrees C with sufficient H-2 fuel.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With a lower H-2 flow rate, SOFC fabricated without Fe2O3 shows fluctuating and lowered fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SOFC fabricated with 5 wt% Fe2O3 shows stable and improved performance.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The dense percolation of spherical shaped macropores and a well-connected electrical conduction path, both of which are formed by adding Fe2O3, result in lowered charge and mass transfer polarization, which increase the fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, as a result of the increased charge transfer polarization, the addition of 20 wt% Fe2O3 results in Fe diffusion into the anode functional layer and reduces the fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To obtain improved and stable fuel cell performance, the development of spherical shaped macropores is beneficial and the addition of other elements should be considered.
Titulo: Spherical shaped pore structured cermet supports for solid oxide fuel cells
